Object oriented programming
It basically helps use write large amounts of code. Helps us write large amounts of code.
that is easier to change and manage. There are other ways like functional programming and
procedural programming.
Why should we use OOP
1)Helps use write large amounts of code easily
2)It also helps us represent the world around us inside computers easily.
3)Changing code becomes easier.
4)Sharing code and collaboration becomes easier.
Main concepts/Main pillars of Object Oriented Programming
1) Classes and objects.(Base not considered main pillar)
2) Inheritance.
3)Polymorphism
4)Abstraction
5)Encapsulation
Classes and objects:
A class is like a map/blueprint/idea/design that we create before we start building
the actual object.Classes have properties/ attributes which help us figure out what
something looks like and they have behaviours/functions/methods which helps us understand
how something works.